Nairobi County Governor Mike Sonko has suspended county official over his alleged involvement in approval of buildings on riparian land. Sonko says in a statement from City Hall that the decision precedes his establishment that John Ojwang granted permission for the constructions of South End Mall along Lang’ata Road, and Gem Suits in Riverside Estate. ALSO READ:

Sonko suspends top County directors over laxity Ojwang has been given appeal period for the actions. Statement partly reads: “Mr Ojwang has beeni ssued with  a  notice   to  show  cause within 14 days why disciplinary action should not  be taken against him including termination of employment.” It further reveals that the approvals were made by officials who worked for the Nairobi City council in 1980s and 1990s, and that most of the them have since retired.